Date:  0/0/1904
Source:  Maori Race, The
Author:  TREGEAR
Vol / Page:  40
Edition:
Quote:   [caption] CULTiVATiNG SOiL WiTH THE KO, OR DiGGiNG STiCK. <i>ibid.</i> 321

The principal agricultural tool was the digging- stick (<i>ko</i>), this being a pole or shaft of hard wood from seven to ten feet in length, with a step or foot-rest (<i>hamaruru</i>) lashed on about a foot from the end that entered the ground, this end being pointed or with an edge at foot and sides.
