Quote:  The <i>ko</i> was about seven feet long, sharp at the digging end, with a step or rest for the foot about a foot from the point. The top of the <i>ko</i>  was slightly curved, and it was often carved into the form of a head. [sic] and adorned with feathers. it was also a custom of the <i>ko</i> -men to decorate the top of the implement, near the head, with <i>aurei</i>, the bone mat-pins formerly commonly used, ...
